The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Healthy rise in HDIL net profit
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                             Healthy rise in HDIL net profit
                            
	Mumbai, May 21 (PTI): Housing Development amp; Infrastructure Ltd (HDIL) has posted a consolidated net profit of Rs 1,409.84 crore for the year ended March 31, 2008 compared with Rs 548 crore a year ago, an increase of 157 per cent, the firm said in a filing to the Bombay Stock Exchange (BSE).        
	HDILs revenue rose to Rs 2,433.29 crore in 2007-08 from Rs 1,224.79 crore in the previous fiscal.The company posted a net profit of Rs 1,410.50 crore for the reporting period, a two-fold rise from Rs 541.82 crore in the previous year.        
	The firms revenue increased to Rs 2,432.32 crore during 2007-08 from Rs 1,216.51 crore in the preceding fiscal. For the quarter ended March 31, HDIL posted a net profit of Rs 708.25 crore and revenues of Rs 989.49 crore.        
	HDILs board of directors has approved a bonus issue in the proportion of two new equity shares for every seven equity shares held. It has also recommended a final dividend of Rs 3 per share.        
	Shares of the company closed at Rs 811.75, down 3.64 per cent on the BSE.                                                                                                                                     
